  <ToolSection
    class='mb-5'
    title='Environment'
    tools={[
      {
        name: 'macOS',
        description: 'Mac Mini M4',
        href: 'https://www.apple.com/macos/',
        icon: import('@/assets/tools/apple.svg?raw')
      },
      {
        name: 'Ubuntu 24.04.2 LTS',
        description: 'Linux Distribution',
        href: 'https://ubuntu.com/',
        icon: import('@/assets/tools/ubuntu.svg?raw')
      }
    ]}
  />

  {/* social-networks */}
  <h2 id='social-networks'>Social Networks</h2>
  <p>
    Find me around the web — I'm most active on GitHub and X, and I occasionally post on Bilibili
    and Xiaohongshu.
  </p>
  <Substats
    stats={[
      {
        platform: 'GitHub',
        icon: 'github',
        link: 'https://github.com/joyehuang',
        text: 'followers',
        api: 'github/joyehuang'
      },
      {
        platform: 'Bilibili',
        icon: 'bilibili',
        color: '#e71f19',
        link: 'https://space.bilibili.com/406318693',
        text: 'followers',
        api: 'bilibili/406318693'
      },
      {
        platform: 'Xiaohongshu',
        icon: '/src/assets/icons/xiaohongshu.png',
        color: '#fe2c55',
        link: 'https://www.xiaohongshu.com/user/profile/65a14d170000000022017286?xsec_token=YBPKP2bQlVpuT_aLOsY5GdFkn_DdrD6hHVzbyZjzFcMTg=&xsec_source=app_share&xhsshare=CopyLink&appuid=65a14d170000000022017286&apptime=1752108974&share_id=2fdaa435651f421f80142ff6608a1d64',
        text: 'followers',
        count: 1572
      },
      {
        platform: 'X (Twitter)',
        icon: 'x',
        color: '#000000',
        link: 'https://x.com/deshiou0604',
        text: 'followers',
        count: 57
      }
    ]}
  />

  {/* gossips */}
  <h2 id='gossips'>Gossips</h2>
  <Collapse title='Life in Melbourne'>
    Life as a student in Melbourne is both full and fun. The coffee culture, the street art, and the
    mix of cultures all draw me in. On weekends I'll walk along St Kilda beach or spend the whole
    day at the State Library. I miss home every so often, but this chapter has grown me a lot.
  </Collapse>
  <Collapse title='About Internship'>
    I'm lucky to intern in Tezign's AIGC R&D team, where I finally get hands-on with frontier AI in
    real products. Great team, patient mentors — and a lot of practical experience you just can't
    pick up in a classroom.
  </Collapse>
  <Collapse title='About Music'>
    Though my parents "made" me learn instruments, I'm grateful they held the line. Piano taught me
    how to express feeling; cello taught me patience and focus. When debugging fries my brain, a
    few minutes on the keys works better than coffee.
  </Collapse>

  {/* about-blog */}
  <h2 id='about-blog'>About Blog</h2>
  <p>
    This blog is my space for technical notes and life updates. It mostly covers what I'm learning
    and building around agents, LLM internals, and full-stack work — with occasional notes from
    internships and stray thoughts along the way. Writing is how I turn experience into knowledge,
    and hopefully some of it helps others on the same path.
  </p>
  <p>
    The principle behind the site: keep it simple, fast, and content-first. Modern stack,
    fast loads, no friction. Comments welcome — let's learn together.
  </p>
  <p>Website history:</p>
  <Timeline
    events={[
      {
        date: '2025-07-04',
        content:
          'Launched the personal blog with <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank">Astro</a> + <a href="https://github.com/cworld1/astro-theme-pure" target="_blank">Pure Theme</a>, deployed to Vercel.'
      },
      {
        date: '2025-07-01',
        content:
          'Published my first post, "My first PR" — the official start of writing here.'
      },
      {
        date: '2025-10-23',
        content:
          'Wrote "A frontend intern\u2019s interview guide for Chinese startups", lessons and prep notes.'
      },
      {
        date: '2025-12',
        content:
          'Kicked off the LLM internals series: deep-dive notes on RMSNorm, RoPE, Attention, and FeedForward — the four pillars of a Transformer block.'
      },
      {
        date: '2026-03-09',
        content:
          'Published "An Agent dev interview handbook for a second-year intern"; the blog\u2019s focus officially shifted toward agent development.'
      },
      {
        date: '2026-04-10',
        content:
          'Started a source-reading series — beginning with OpenHarness to study how agent harnesses are implemented.'
      }
    ]}
  />
  <p>
    The smooth operation and personalized customization of this site also rely on the resources and
    technical support from the following excellent projects and service providers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Framework & Theme: <a href='https://astro.build/' target='_blank'>Astro</a> + <a
        href='https://github.com/cworld1/astro-theme-pure'
        target='_blank'>Astro Theme Pure</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      Site hosting: <a href='https://vercel.com/' target='_blank'>Vercel</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      Other statistics: <a href='https://github.com/spencerwooo/substats' target='_blank'
        >Substats</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>
</PageLayout>
